-- Vietnam's BIDV sees 2014 gross profit up 13.4 pct y/y
-- By Ho Binh Minh
-- Fri Apr 25, 2014 02:57AM EDT
-- None



HANOI, April 25 (Reuters) - The Bank for Investment and Development of Vietnam <BID.HM>(BIDV), the country's third-largest lender by assets, said on Friday its gross profit this year is expected to rise 13.4 percent from 2013 to 6 trillion dong ($284 million).

